Sofiane Boufal scored as Morocco began the Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) with a hard-fought win over Ghana just as Sadio Mane converted a penalty more than six minutes into injury time as Senegal escaped with a 1-0 win over Zimbabwe to open their campaign. Also yesterday, Guinea edged out Malawi 1-0 at the Kouekong Stadium in Bafoussam as Issiaga Sylla became the hero for the National Elephants as the left-back scored the only goal of the match which earned his side a win in the opening game of Group B. Meanwhile, Boufal, former Southampton winger , with only eight minutes to play to settle a cagey heavyweight contest in the Cameroonian capital of Yaounde.   Nigeria faces testy tie against Egypt in AFCON     Eguavoen: Eagles’ win greater than personal glory     Eagles ‘ll tame Salah,  says Simon   The Moroccan hammered home from close range after a mazy run into the penalty area from Zakaria Aboukhlal that saw him tease the Ghana defence, only to be checked by Arsenal midfielder Thomas Partey, with the ball then running perfectly for Boufal to score. - Advertisement - Elsewhere, Mane sent the goalkeeper the wrong way and drilled the penalty into the left-hand corner after Senegal produced a misfiring first performance in Cameroon for much of the game. Senegal never looked like Africa’s top-ranked team, nor a team playing an opposition ranked 101 places below them.